{"parse":{"title":"Bedlam: London and Its Mad","pageid":46633182,"revid":785117789,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Bedlam: London and Its Mad <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Bedlam%3A+London+and+Its+Mad&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BCatharine+Arnold%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.pub=Pocket+Books+%28Simon+and+Schuster%29&amp;rft.pages=306\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Bedlam_(book).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Bedlam (book).jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/69/Bedlam_%28book%29.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"311\" data-file-width=\"200\" data-file-height=\"311\" /></a><div>Cover of the first edition</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Catharine_Arnold\" title=\"Catharine Arnold\">Catharine Arnold</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUnited Kingdom</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Subject</th><td>\nHistory of mental illness and treatment of mental illness, <a href=\"/wiki/Bethlem_Hospital\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bethlem Hospital\">Bethlem Hospital</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Set&#160;in</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/London\" title=\"London\">London</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Published</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/London\" title=\"London\">London</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\nPocket Books (Simon and Schuster)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n2008</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nPrint</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n306</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781847390004\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781847390004\">9781847390004</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Dewey_Decimal_Classification\" title=\"Dewey Decimal Classification\">Dewey Decimal</a></div></th><td>\n362.210942109</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Bedlam: London and Its Mad</b></i> is a 2008 book by <a href=\"/wiki/British_people\" title=\"British people\">British</a> author, academic and journalist <a href=\"/wiki/Catharine_Arnold\" title=\"Catharine Arnold\">Catharine Arnold</a>. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Synopsis\">Synopsis</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bedlam:_London_and_Its_Mad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Synopsis\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The book follow developments in societal treatment of mental illness and the mentally ill, from the cruel days of <a href=\"/wiki/Bethlem_Hospital\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bethlem Hospital\">Bethlem Hospital</a> (often known as \"Bedlam\") to the campaigning psychiatrists who secured advances in treatment and changes in societal viewpoints. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reception\">Reception</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bedlam:_London_and_Its_Mad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Reception\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Guardian\" title=\"The Guardian\">The Guardian</a></i>, Patrick McGrath made some criticisms of the book, arguing 'Arnold occasionally makes wild claims' but notes that the strength of the book is 'the author indulges all that is quirky and macabre in the fascinating story of madness in England',<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> while in the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Daily_Mail\" title=\"Daily Mail\">Daily Mail</a></i> Maureen Walker described the book as a 'elegantly written and richly anecdotal study'.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\nThe <i>Psychiatric Times</i> was rather more critical, with the reviewer writing 'Is Bedlam accurate, historically reliable, and of academic and therapeutic value? I think not' and 'In the final page of the book, we discover that \u201cover the years, [the author has] learned to embrace melancholy,\u201d and \u201csome of us prefer to endure \u2018melancholy\u2019 in its various manifestations and accept that this variety of madness is part of our identity.\u201d A \u201cGovernment Health Warning\u201d should accompany this frank, therapeutic nihilism and negativity toward psychiatric treatment'.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bedlam:_London_and_Its_Mad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/books/2008/aug/23/nonfiction.books\">https://www.theguardian.com/books/2008/aug/23/nonfiction.books</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/home/books/article-1042885/Bedlam-brutal-truth.html\">http://www.dailymail.co.uk/home/books/article-1042885/Bedlam-brutal-truth.html</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.psychiatrictimes.com/film-and-book-reviews/bedlam-london-and-its-mad\">http://www.psychiatrictimes.com/film-and-book-reviews/bedlam-london-and-its-mad</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1246\nCached time: 20180908212511\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.116 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.164 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 942/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 6974/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1423/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 20/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1321/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 1/400\nLua time usage: 0.032/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.44 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  140.826      1 -total\n 93.58%  131.787      1 Template:Infobox_book\n 68.92%   97.062      1 Template:Infobox\n 21.71%   30.580      1 Template:ISBNT\n 20.10%   28.299      1 Template:ISBN\n 15.28%   21.520      1 Template:Wikidata_image\n  8.72%   12.275      1 Template:Catalog_lookup_link\n  4.70%    6.617      1 Template:Reflist\n  4.14%    5.830      1 Template:Error-small\n  3.44%    4.849      3 Template:Yesno-no\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:46633182-0!canonical and timestamp 20180908212511 and revision id 785117789\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"Pages_to_import_images_to_Wikid